# 🌍 Global Happiness and Prosperity Trends (2015–2024)

## 📘 Project Overview

This project explores global happiness trends and economic prosperity between 2015 and 2024 using data from the World Happiness Report. It combines Python-based preprocessing with interactive Tableau visualizations to deliver insights into regional well-being and GDP dynamics.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- Analyze and visualize happiness scores across countries and regions
- Track changes in average happiness over time
- Identify the top 10 wealthiest countries by GDP per capita
- Uncover geographic patterns in happiness and prosperity

---

## 🛠 Tools & Technologies

| Component       | Tool/Library            |
|------------------|--------------------------|
| Data Processing  | Python (pandas, numpy)   |
| Visualization    | Tableau Desktop Public   |
| Plotting (optional) | matplotlib, seaborn   |
| Data Source      | World Happiness Report (2015–2024) |

---

## 📊 Key Features of the Dashboard

### 1. **Happiness Score Map**
- Displays 2024 global happiness scores by country
- Blue = higher scores, Red = lower scores
- Insight: Europe, Oceania top scorers; Sub-Saharan Africa lowest

### 2. **Happiness Trend by Region**
- Line chart of happiness scores from 2015–2024
- Tracks long-term regional shifts
- North America, Latin America consistently high; Southern Asia lags

### 3. **Top 10 Countries by GDP per Capita**
- Bar chart ranking the wealthiest countries (2024)
- Includes Luxembourg, Singapore, UAE, Switzerland, Ireland, etc.

